    "notes": "Week 7 Day 2 of Talk 5 (Week 1 of 1, Single-Week Talk). Mental Models focus: Extracting key mental models from Munger's educational reform manifesto. Core frameworks: Man-with-a-Hammer Syndrome (over-reliance on familiar tools), Fundamental Four-Discipline Combination (Math, Physics, Chemistry, Engineering as bedrock), Aircraft Simulator Analogy (knowledge maintenance through regular practice), Four Types of Checklists (Two-Track Analysis, Investing Checklist, Five Notions, 25 Psychology Tendencies), Principle of Economy (use fundamental principles before creating new complexity). 5 case snapshots - LTCM collapse (finance-only expertise without multidisciplinary perspective), Quibi's $1.75B failure (content-only model ignored psychology/sociology/economics), Software engineer who only knows code (programming expert treating every problem as technical), Berkshire's See's Candies acquisition (multidisciplinary lollapalooza), CEO who optimized only one metric (growth hammer ignored economics/psychology/strategy). 5 actionable takeaways including audit problem-solving approach, Two-Track Analysis checklist, identify man-with-a-hammer areas, build simulator routine, Principle of Economy bias countermeasure. Mental model drill on Man-with-a-Hammer Syndrome + Multidisciplinary Coverage. 3 reflection questions on self-audit, environment/culture, latticework building. Personal commitment: Analyze one problem using 3 different disciplinary models (15-20 min). Talk 5 Day 2 complete. Next: Day 3 Inversion focus. Message delivered successfully."
